The '''India U-23''' is the national team which represents [[India]] at U-23 level. India U-23 participated in [[Asian Games]]. They are also a dominant force in [[South Asian Games]].
==History== ===Olympics=== ====2012 Olympics==== In order for India U-23 to qualify for the [[2012 Olympics]] they would have to get past the qualifiers. In the first round India U-23 played the Myanmar U-23 squad and won on aggregate 3-2. They then faced Qatar U-23 in the second round and lost 4-2 on aggregate. With this lost India U-23 were out of the running for the Olympics.
===South Asian Football Federation Cup=== ====SAFF Cup 2009==== The [[All India Football Federation]] have planned to send the U-23 squad to [[2009 South Asian Football Federation Cup|SAFF Cup 2009]] in order to provide adequate exposure, the federation also wanted to find few possible talents for [[Asian Cup 2011]] in [[Qatar]]. India U-23 started off the tournament with a 1-0 win against [[Afghanistan national football team|Afghanistan]], they then won their second match 1-0 against [[Nepal national football team|Nepal]]. They then lost 2-0 to [[Maldives national football team|Maldives]] but managed to qualified for the Semi-Finals with two wins. India U-23 then met the hosts [[Bangladesh national football team|Bangladesh]] in the semis and managed to pull a surprise 1-0 win with their best performance of the tournament. India U-23 met [[Maldives national football team|Maldives]] in the finals and managed to win the match via penalties after being 0-0 after the extra time, with this win India U-23 pocketed its 5th title.
